I will save you all from a long post, since this isn't my board.  But I would like to see your ability to hold agro improved.  I would say if they gave you guys 80% of the agro holding ability of say an SK/Pally in an xp group that would be fair.<br>
<br>
From the posts earlier, while true it is the caster's fault he is getting agro, it is also a huge PITA for the caster to group with a warrior over a pally/sk right now due to agro issues.<br>
<br>
Barjam<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soulflayerdwagonslayer>Soulflayer Dwagonslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/14/03 6:53:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> Warriors, despite all the work Verant has done in PoP with them still need help. Yes there are other classes that could use help but since this is warrior board we'll keep it only pertained to this class. <br>
<br>
[b]DEFENSE SKILLS[/b]<br>
<br>
Honestly, like Furor said &quot; we need our own mitigation table &quot;. As the warrior should really stand out in his class vs others.<br>
<br>
Remove Defensive and Aggressive as a discipline. Instead make the warrior unique vs any other class by giving them a sliding bar to set their play style to the mob at hand. To the far left is full defensive where you take less and do less, the center which is you do full damage and mitigate as normal and to the far right is aggressive where you do more damage and take more in return. This can be altered at any time. <br>
<br>
Shields should all incorperate furious bash of the highest level when any warrior wields, reguardless of level. ALSO while using a shield the warrior  gains the ability of Block. The higher the level of warrior the higher the skill, thus a level 65 Warrior with a shield would have a 250 Block while wielding a shield which is balanced for losing DPS of a offhand weapon and is incentive to use one.<br>
<br>
Shield Skill. Only needs a little tuning where a person in defensive should be able to shield player. Other then that the skill is pretty good, though I would like a timer like a /dis to show me how much time I have left till its ready again.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tactical Mastery Skill: Even at level 3 its ungodly how often mobs can dodge, parry and riposte. Turn the misses on and become quickly demoralized. This skill needs some help. Please retune it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hit points if the system should stay as is should be raised drastically for the warrior IF that is how the class is defined. 65 Warrior wearing the very best of every item should be a few thousand hitpoints higher then any other class. NOW if you used the skills I mention in this post then the hit points as they stand is fine. Best Magelo Warrior vs Best Magelo Paladin the difference is only by 500ish hit points. Though I hope their is more to the class of a warrior then a few hundred more hp and defense / evassive disciplines.<br>
<br>
Taunt. Ah the key that you only hit in frustration cuz it says  TAUNT. Personally I think Verant put that key in the game as a sick joke vs Warriors. They say if we could get agro at any time the game is broken, but its ok for Paladins to hold agro as they tank better in xp groups then us, and are better tanks vs boss mobs that dont require defensive to win. Nerfing the Paladin isn't the answer, stuns is part of their class BUT the taunt button for a warrior should have the agro of a stun, just not the effects. Enraging Blow weapon while nice, requires you to get &quot; lucky &quot; and hit a proc to help get you agro and isnt a sure thing on proc. Most Warriors will never see that kind of weapon nor should it be necessary for warriors to do thier job, which is tank.<br>
<br>
Area Effect Taunt: One of our best AA skills yet is a joke with a 15 minute reuse time, 10ish with additional AA skills. Make it 5 Minutes and 2.5 Minutes with AA skills. Don't tell me that would be broken either, Healing Wave of Marr/Prexus from a Paladin is AE Taunt with a faster refresh time and heal to boot.<br>
<br>
<br>
[b]Offensive Skills[/b]<br>
<br>
Flurry. Great skill when you see how a mob uses it, but a joke when you see how often it goes off for a warrior. This skill is linked as a chance to go off when a triple attack is scored but should be changed to check for when a double attack goes off instead. Higher Dex should also help increase in the skill going off, thus being crippled would lower the chances.<br>
<br>
Fury. We were once the only class with this eye candy skill. Since most of us use 1H weapons the crits did very little to boost DPS, with 2H you could see a improvement on DPS. Other classes that do more damage in larger chunks can make far better use out of this then us. With Fury of the Ages warriors should have a chance to also turn their Crits into Crippling hits, reguardless of where their life is at.<br>
<br>
2H weapons: This goes for every class that can use. Verant you have made alot of high damage 2H with delays dropping below 28 which is the old cut off level for high damage bonus's. Having a 2H weapon with 40 Damage and 25 Delay is CRAP if the damage bonus is only 14, like a 1H weapon. Hell many Knight class's call em crap loot and continue to use their Golden Rods, which should tell ya something since the Cursed Cycle is now very gimp compared to PoP Bosses. Please go back and recalibur these new 2H in PoP.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In PoP the items are for the most part CRAP. The items in Tier 1 through 3 are garbage for the most part ( 90% of the items ) if you have any VT gear for the risk vs reward.In the Elemental planes we get our best shoulders which have, get this, ONLY 25 FEKING AC on the puresteel pauldrons and have fun killing the mob that drops em. Was the AC cap raised? Appears so, that at 1800 and 2000 seems to have noticable differences. Be warned! AC items in PoP are horrible! Not only do they have horrible AC but the risk vs reward is not just and needs some serious work. Elemental Armor is where its at BUT the items are not on your standard yard trash which hit in the 900 range along with special abilities but off rare names ( several day spawns )! Even those nameds don't always drop Elemental Armor. Legs and BP (is unsure at this time) only drop off the last Boss in each elemental zone, and even then its a random type of leg and its not a sure drop. How many people wear plate in your guild? <br>
<br>
Bottom line is the warriors, as I mentioned as have other posts before mine, still need some help. Also developers need to go through PoP and adjust the items stats / effects and weigh them properly for risk vs reward.<br>
<br>
<br>
Note: I mention several comparisons vs Paladins. This isn't an attempt to nerf them but I look at what they do well. Hopefully through comparisons Sony will decide to help warriors, NOT to nerf Paladins.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 276<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/03 7:53:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>AC items in PoP are horrible!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
