<br>
The penalty already comes into play when you enter the stance. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you aren't getting hit, what is the penalty for reducing your defense by 20-30%? If you were able to switch instantly, there would essentially be no penalty at all for being in aggressive stance. As soon as you got aggro, you would be able to switch instantly into defensive. The negative effects of being in the aggressive stance would be pointless.<br>
<br>
I don't think having some kind of time dependent restriction on it (within reason) would remove its usefullness. Being able to specialize for either damage output or tanking ability without having to burn a /disc would be a massive improvement. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Crusader of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zhaun>Zhaun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/03 3:29:34 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> I see why some kind of time restriction on switching modes would be a problem, I think that is just a balance though. Being able to switch at will removes any kind of skill from using the ability. &quot;I'm not getting hit&quot; *click* Agressive. &quot;I'm getting hit&quot; *click* Defensive. Kinda boring to me.<br>
<br>
Now, if there was a time per setting to switch, then it would require more forethought, on the other hand if there was too much of a switch it would really hurt. Say it takes 10seconds (as an example, dunno how goo that number really is) to switch and there is 5 settings for the &quot;switch&quot; (Frenzy, Agressive, Normal, Evasive, Defensive):<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Example1</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
WarriorA is Tanking AoW (just as an example) he is on Defensive for the first few seconds of the fight until the Rotation can get started. At that point if he is feeling confident he can shift up one level to Evasive to improve his DPS/Agro. If the raid is short on healers or there is bad lag, he can stay on Defensive to make it easier on the healers.<br>
<br>
WarriorB is second on the Main Tank list and is not tanking. He stays at Evasive attack setting so he is dealing Ok damage but if WarriorA falls he can step in with AE Taunt, grab agro and already be iin Evasive mode and only be 10seconds away from Defensive mode to help the CHeal Rotation start back up.<br>
<br>
WarriorC is like 5th on the Tank list, he should never have to tank (we hope) so he starts off in Frenzied mode to get the best DPS he can out. He has to be careful about getting on Rampage becasue he is 20seconds away from having no defense penalty (in Normal mode) and may very well be dead in those 20 seconds from a healthy Rampage or two. Also, as the fight goes on and tanks start dropping, WarriorC can slowly edge himself down from Frenzied mode so that by the time he is next in line to tank he will hopefulling be ready in Evasive mode or at least close to it.<br>
<br>
Sounds a hell of a lot more fun and interesting than turning on autoattack and going AFK to me.<br>
<br>
How about XP groups?:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Example2</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:<br>
<br>
WarriorA goes out to pull, and slides to full Defensive mode in case anything unfortunate happens on the pull. He finds a mob and brings it back, he starts the 10second slide into Evasive mode and stays in Evasive mode for the Cleric and Slower to get thier groove going and then has the choice of staying Evasive or sliding up or down depending on the mob difficulty.<br>
<br>
WarriorB in the group stands around waiting for WarriorA to bring the pull in in Normal mode. This way, if things turn to @#%$ in the first few seconds of the mob hitting the camp (not that that ever happens) he is able to bang out AE Taunt and start tanking sliding into Evasive mode. If things are fine he can slide himself up into Agressive or Frenzied mode (depending on zone, group, etc) and actually deal some decent DPS.<br>
<br>
Wow, sounds a lot better to me. An alternate way would be able to instantly Switch one spot over but not be able to switch again for several seconds. This would have good and bad as well. Instant switching is fast reaction but if you're not within one &quot;step&quot; of where you need to be you may be screwed. Eitherway, the delay is important to the &quot;strategy&quot; of using it and will be another thing to make the real, skilled Warriors stand out from the WarBots and WarGimps<br>
<br>
Just change the Disciplines this intrudes on into short (15-30sec?) versions that stack with this &quot;Stance Slider&quot; and wow, you got some pretty cool stuff going. Sure, a Warrior may then be able to have somthing like 50% or 70% mitigation or damage increase for a few seconds but I don't see that as a horrible thing. Warriors should tank like champs and kick a little ass when needed.<br>
<br>
Sorry for the rambling, the idea just stuck in my head and had to get it out. I doubt this is a reasonably expected change they would do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soulflayerdwagonslayer>Soulflayer Dwagonslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/03 4:34:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> The reason for having fast changes is that once you get agro, you will take a set of hits before you can make the change. You wont see it comming as you can't see where you stand on the mobs agro list and you will get a full round of attacks against you. In PoP at the upper levels of play, one round of attacks at an adjusted 20 to 30% more damage will kill a Warrior flat out.<br>
<br>
Take for example Offassa in Plane of Water. He is a mob that hits for 2k x4, Flurrys and has a AE DoT that reduces AC, HP, Mana and Slows. Lets say you have 6 Warriors present at the raid. You will not see any of them use aggressive if its a 15 second to 30 second change, as Offassa can one round a 10k hp tank, so all the Warriors other then MT will be doing really nothing during this time. If they all stay in defensive they lose ALOT of DPS, if they go aggressive they wont make the switch in time to defensive. The change of stances does nothing to mobs that AE Rampage other then the warrior will probably be fighting in a regular ( non bonus ) stance. Even the XP mobs in the Elemental Planes hit for 600 to 900 fairly fast and mitigate slow, lose the Tank and the warrior who is in aggressive will get pulverized when he gets hit as those 900 point hits are turned into 1200 point hits. Gain a add while fighting and if it by chance gains agro on the warrior in aggressive then you can pretty much write him off.<br>
<br>
IF a pause was needed after play testing, then maybe a 5 second pause where the warrior loses the ability to attack for 5 seconds to make the change. Thus for those 5 seconds he stuck in his old stance. 5 seconds might not seem long but thats usually 2 to 3 full set of attacks, not to mention loss of DPS during that time. This would allow warriors in a raid who are 4th or further down the MT line to adjust their play style to be an offensive warrior to help DPS in raid, rather then adding lag.<br>
<br>
Any ways this was a fun idea to come up with. I highly doubt Verant / Sony would ever consider it as they see no problem with the warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=treage>Treage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/03 4:50:35 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> Make it so the ability can't be switched once engaged in combat and the mob is still alive. This way the warrior would have to decide before hand what stance they would like to take. This would remove the trivial &quot;getting hit slide to defensive, not getting hit slide to aggresive&quot; mid swing scenerio from the equation.<br>
